5:
I think I understand the situation.
Thank you for sharing such
information, Your Highness.
7:
You say that Palpebra is no enemy
of ours. Therefore, I assume, you
want us to take the soldiers who are
patrolling the border and dispatch
them to help the Nouins.
10:
House Nouin won't hold out much
longer by themselves. And should
they fall, the people will fall with
them.
15:
I understand your concern. But I am
afraid that I cannot acquiesce to
your request, Your Highness.
19:
Wh-why not? Are you suspicious of
Palpebra too?!
22:
Not at all. If I may, I would go so far
as to say that a betrayal on their
part is entirely out of the question.
25:
I stand by what I witnessed during
the dreadful events at the
ceremony. Let the Oxtans believe
what they may.
32:
That we patrol the border is His
Majesty's wish.
35:
As the King's sword, we must abide
by his orders, regardless of our
personal feelings on the matter.
40:
Ciel, what are you saying?! Will you
just follow any order blindly?!
43:
And, more importantly, does House
Nouin even know of this?
46:
Protecting order in the Farlands is
their duty. Accepting our help would
be akin to ceding their duty.
48:
Tell me, Yuwel. Does House Nouin
want to rely on the Tris' to cover their
shortcomings?
52:
If I know my brother, he would not
accept that.
56:
Then why have you approached me
first? You cannot keep acting as a
knight with no ruler.
64:
How can you accept this, Cieldeau?
Are you a leader who will ignore the
cries of your people?!
67:
The path ahead should be clear to
all of us! The Nouins, Kweturs, and
Oxtans too! Why are you so blind?!
76:
Whatever the truth, the Kweturs and
Oxtans' opinions are influencing
both His Majesty and the council.
78:
They will need reason enough to
change their views.
82:
So... if they had such a reason, you
think that they would yield?
87:
If you need a reason to give them, I
can provide you with one.
91:
The more time we waste, the more
our kingdom keeps bleeding out.
97:
I remember you... You are from
House Oxtan. What are you doing
here? Can't you see I am speaking
with His Highness?
105:
It is an honor to meet you, Your
Highness. My name is Marden Oxtan.
108:
As the second son of my house, I am
a lowly priest. I have come to offer
you what little help I can.
112: Why would an Oxtan want to help us?
117:
We are playing politics here,
correct? Long story short, all we
have to do is to shut both the
Kweturs and my own house up.
120:
Now, tell me, have you ever heard of
the Star Augurs?
125:
What? Are those some sort of
oracles from your house?
129:
I see. You may be the only one here
who does not know about them,
Your Highness.
132:
Sparing you the details, they are a
shady organization come here from
a foreign land. They are known all
the way to Palpebra.
134:
Some say that they are performing
strange experiments with monsters.
137:
What's more, rumor has it that they
have certain questionable dealings
with the Kweturs and my own family.
142:
We have no time to waste listening
to the ramblings of strange priests.
Yuwel?
151:
Hahaha, of course a lord would
disregard such conspiracy theories.
Perhaps I also approached the
wrong one first.
154:
Very well. Perhaps you two could
lend me your time instead?
159:
Orgus Oxtan? The Farlana priest
who was removed from his post?
163:
Precisely. He is my uncle, and also
one of the people suspected of
attacking the peace treaty
ceremony.
166:
Unbelievable... Do you speak the
truth?
170:
Yes, although this was never
officially disclosed. But this seems to
ring a bell with you, Yuwel Nouin.
175:
He is not lying, Your Highness. And
the people he was working for, if
memory serves, were the Star
Augurs.
178:
How was this incident explained to
the rest of the Farlands?
181:
Well, it wasn't. If I may venture a
guess, the Kweturs are to blame.
184:
House Oxtan tried to make as little
fuss as possible too. My uncle was
confined to a mansion and any
investigations were called off in light
of his allegedly unstable condition.
188:
But why are you trying to uncover
the misdeeds of your own house?
What is your motive?
192:
Well... Is the fact that I loved my
uncle not reason enough?
195:
He was a devout follower of Farlana.
As devout as he was foolish. I want
him to be redeemed.
200:
I see. You're striving to save those
close to you too.
204:
We welcome your help, Marden! Let
us save Orgus together!
208: Thank you, Your Highness! I love you!
216: Seriously? I didn't sign up for this.
220: Vyron! What are you doing here?!
224:
Oh, you know our mercenary? From
your time in Palpebra, perhaps?
227: Whatever the case, Vyron is all yours!
